{Show the right plan for Black.} 10... Bd7 $1 {The best move in this position.
Black leaves the e6-square for the knight and prepares 11...0-0-0[%cal Ge8c8]}
11. c3 Ne6 $1 {The point of Black's move 10 is to leave the square empty for
the knight.} 12. Bxf6 gxf6 13. Qf3 {How to protect the f6-pawn?} Nf4 $1 {Very
strong move. Now 14.g3 is well met by  14...Nh3 followed by Ng5. Black has
more than enough counterplay in this position.} *

