{What Black should play?} 10... Be6 $1 {Getting rid of White's pressure along
the a2-g8 diagonal is one of Black's essential ideas in this variation.} 11.
Bc2 {If White avoids the exchange of the light-squared bishops, then Black can
seize the initiative by playing...} d5 {Thematic reaction. Now Black enjoys a
space advantage in the centre.} 12. exd5 Bxd5 $1 13. b4 Ba7 $1 14. a4 {How to
stop the b4-b5 threat?} b5 $1 {Another thematic move for the variation. The
activity of his pieces, gives Black better prospects.} *

