{How to deal with the threat of Ng3-f5?} 13... Bf8 $1 {In this variation the
f8-square is a perfect spot for the bishop. From this position, it controls
the queenside and participates in the defence.  This is an idea that you
should remember!} 14. Ng3 g6 $1 {The f5-square is covered and the h6 pawn is
protected. It is not obvious what White will do with this knight on g3.} *

